<h3> Variable Assign: Aleph/Aleff </h3>

Greetings Tom!

<a href="https://sophiaz-library-version-1.neocities.org/Sophia's%20Library%20Version%201/Construction/Essential%20&%20Remaining/E%20&%20R/Oct%209_Try2Fin/Jude_BOOM">
May mercy, peace and love be yours in abundance.
- (Jude 2)</a>

I wish you well.
(Click on the Blue links below for any additional content.)

Now that you have read my fictional short story, 'Short Story #2: <a href="https://israeljoshuajennin7.wixsite.com/sword-and-hammer/single-post/2017/11/16/short-story-2">
Isaiah's Conversion</a>', you might compare it to the historical account (in the <a href="https://sophiaz-library-version-2.neocities.org/Bible_Formal%20and%20Functional_BOOM">Bible</a>) from which i drew inspiration.  Some of the most pertinent sections are the following:
<ul>

<li> 2nd Kings (Chapters)<a href="https://sophiaz-library-version-1.neocities.org/Sophia's%20Library%20Version%201/Construction/OT/2nd%20Kings/2nd%20Kings%20Ch%2018_BOOM">
18</a>, <a href="https://sophiaz-library-version-1.neocities.org/Sophia's%20Library%20Version%201/Construction/OT/2nd%20Kings/2nd%20Kings%20Ch%2019_BOOM"> 19</a>, and <a href="https://sophiaz-library-version-1.neocities.org/Sophia's%20Library%20Version%201/Construction/OT/2nd%20Kings/2nd%20Kings%20Ch%2020_BOOM">20</a></li>

<li><a href="https://sophiaz-library-version-1.neocities.org/Sophia's%20Library%20Version%201/Construction/OT/2nd%20Chron/2nd%20Chronicles%20Chapter%2029_BOOM">
2nd Chronicles 29</a>,<a href="https://sophiaz-library-version-1.neocities.org/Sophia's%20Library%20Version%201/Construction/OT/2nd%20Chron/2nd%20Chronicles%20Chapter%2030_BOOM">30</a>, <a href="https://sophiaz-library-version-1.neocities.org/Sophia's%20Library%20Version%201/Construction/OT/2nd%20Chron/2nd%20Chronicles%20Chapter%2031_BOOM">31</a> and <a href="https://sophiaz-library-version-1.neocities.org/Sophia's%20Library%20Version%201/Construction/OT/2nd%20Chron/2nd%20Chronicles%20Chapter%2032_BOOM">32</a></li> and 

<li> <a href="https://jeshroomnsophieshouse.neocities.org/New%20Cubes_August%202025/August%203rd%20and%204th/August%203/Isaiah_BOOM%20files/ch%2021-66/Isaiah_36_Closer_BOOM">Isaiah 36</a>, <a href="https://jeshroomnsophieshouse.neocities.org/New%20Cubes_August%202025/August%203rd%20and%204th/August%203/Isaiah_BOOM%20files/ch%2021-66/Isaiah_37_Closer_BOOM">Isaiah 37</a>, <a href="https://jeshroomnsophieshouse.neocities.org/New%20Cubes_August%202025/August%203rd%20and%204th/August%203/Isaiah_BOOM%20files/ch%2021-66/Isaiah_38_Closer_BOOM">Isaiah 38</a> and <a href="https://jeshroomnsophieshouse.neocities.org/New%20Cubes_August%202025/August%203rd%20and%204th/August%203/Isaiah_BOOM%20files/Isaiah_10_Closer_BOOM">10</a>. </li>
</ul>
Of <a href="https://sophiaz-library-version-3.neocities.org/DDC/200/220/DDC_226%20_Gospels%20and%20Acts_New%20Testament_BOOM">the four gospels</a>,
I recommend reading 
<a href="https://jeshroomnsophieshouse.neocities.org/New%20Cubes_August%202025/August%203rd%20and%204th/Mark%20single%20ch%20webpgs/BOOM%20files/Mark%20Chapter%201_cell%20x3y2z3_BOOM">Mark</a> first, then
<a href="https://sophiaz-library-version-2.neocities.org/50/30/z1%20and%20Nav%20Pgs/Mt%20z1_BOOM"> Matthew</a>, then <a href="https://sophiaz-library-version-1.neocities.org/Sophia's%20Library%20Version%201/Construction/Luke/Luke%20Chapters%201-24_BOOM"> Luke</a>, then.<a href="https://sophiaz-library-version-2.neocities.org/50/30/z1%20and%20Nav%20Pgs/Jn%20z1_BOOM"> John</a>.

Of the Epistles, I recommend reading <a href="https://sophiaz-library-version-2.neocities.org/50/30/Mt_Ax/Acts%20z1_BOOM">Acts</a> first and then <a href="https://sophiaz-library-version-2.neocities.org/2026_All%20in/John%20in%20progress_Gospel%20and%20Rev/Rev%20z1_BOOM"> Revelation</a>.

I want to remind you of the 3-1-1 reading pland that has enabled meto read the whole <a href="https://sophiaz-library-version-2.neocities.org/Bible_Formal%20and%20Functional_BOOM">Bible</a> at least nine times in a time span of about ten years:

(Each day read:)
Three chapters of <a href="https://sophiaz-library-version-1.neocities.org/Sophia's%20Library%20Version%201/Construction/DDC_221%20%20Old%20Testament_BOOM"> the Old Testament</a>

One Chapter of <a href="https://sophiaz-library-version-3.neocities.org/DDC/200/220/DDC_226%20_Gospels%20and%20Acts_New%20Testament_BOOM">the four gospels</a>

One Chapter of <a href="https://sophiaz-library-version-1.neocities.org/Sophia's%20Library%20Version%201/Singles%20_Chapters/Other%20Nearby%20Files/all%20epistles_z1%20Page_BOOM"> the Epistles</a>

Here are 2 additional websites:
<a href="https://sophiaz-library-version-3.neocities.org/DDC/200/220/Bible%20ISBN_BOOM"> Click HERE for the Pocket-Sized Bibles ISBN numbers. </a>

<a href="https://www.amazon.com/Holy-Bible-Pocket-Size-International-Version/dp/1558195750/ref=sr_1_1_so_ABIS_BOOK?crid=U23VAG73EG&dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.wBMmKFvYuGJpEGGWELC6yg.7p-nmyCu4zCaBRFPwbecc8mxF2jofefWzhPW6xcFBro&dib_tag=se&keywords=1558195750&nsdOptOutParam=true&qid=1775492565&s=books&sprefix=1558195750%2Cstripbooks%2C173&sr=1-1"> Click HERE to view the Pocket-Sized Bible type I hope to get to you from Amazon. </a>

I hope that you may desire and wish and succeed in entering into God's protected flock by accepting Christ as your Savior and trusting in Him as your sole righteousness before God and committing your life to Him and fully becoming a Christian.  You might call out, "Jesus please save me." if you find a moment when you can be alone.

You can view the main content of the cube by clicking the link to the right of this message text box in Square 6.

My letter to you is continued in the Square below, in Square 8...

